data.title: Distinguished Alumni
data.meta_description: The University of Kansas School of Law established the Distinguished Alumni Award in 1964 to honor outstanding alumni and their contributions to the legal profession.
data.text:
Overview

The KU Law Distinguished Alumni Award is presented annually to KU School of Law graduates who have distinguished themselves through exemplary service to the legal profession, their communities, the university, and the state or country.

Since 1964, the school has honored more than 100 alumni whose lives have benefited the community and whose noteworthy contributions throughout the year have brought honor to the School of Law.
